[[File:John Holmstrom.jpg|thumb|Holmstrom in 2013]]
'''John Holmstrom''' (born 1954) is an American [[underground comix|underground]] [[cartoonist]] and writer. He is best known for illustrating the covers of the [[Ramones]] albums ''[[Rocket to Russia]]'' and ''[[Road to Ruin (Ramones album)|Road to Ruin]]'', as well as his characters Bosko and Joe (published in Scholastic's ''[[Bananas (magazine)|Bananas]]'' magazine from 1975â€“1984).

As the founding editor of ''[[Punk Magazine]]''<ref>{{cite news| url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/entertainment/5263364.stm | work=BBC News | title=Punk rock: 30 years of subversion | date=August 18, 2006}}</ref> at the age of 21 in late 1975, Holmstrom's work became the visual representation of the punk era. After ''Punk'' ceased publication in 1979, he worked for several publications, including ''[[The Village Voice]]'', ''Video Games'' magazine, ''K-Power'', and ''[[Heavy Metal (magazine)|Heavy Metal]]''.

In 1986, Holmstrom contributed a comic-based chronology of punk rock for ''[[Spin (magazine)|Spin]]'' magazine's special punk issue.<ref name="spin1986" /> In 1987, Holmstrom began to work for ''[[High Times]]'' magazine as Managing Editor, was soon promoted to Executive Editor, and in 1991 was promoted to Publisher and President. In 1996 he stepped aside to launch the ''High Times'' website.

He left ''High Times'' in 2000, and went on to work on other projects. He relaunched ''Punk'' for a few issues (before the events of 9/11 ended it), published a Bosko comic book, and got involved in several Japanese clothing deals. He was quoted in a September 2007 [[New York Times]] article about the [[CBGB]].<ref>{{cite news|url= https://www.nytimes.com/2007/09/14/arts/14expl.html?pagewanted=all |work= The New York Times |first= John |last= Strausbaugh |title= Paths of Resistance in the East Village |date= September 14, 2007 |accessdate= 2015-04-09 }}</ref>

==Acting==
Holmstrom has appeared in the films ''School for Vandals'', ''[[End of the Century: The Story of the Ramones]]'', and ''[[Loren Cass]]''.<ref>{{cite news| url=https://movies.nytimes.com/person/524930/John-Holmstrom/filmography | work=The New York Times | title=John Holmstrom}}</ref>

